			<h3 ><a href="#p167667">Re: 日本語 vs 中国語 thread</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=167667&amp;sid=0e85b02fdffd4eb6ce0a97e2778f051d#p167667"><img src="http://thejapanesepage.com/phpbb/styles/tjp-embed/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17039&amp;sid=0e85b02fdffd4eb6ce0a97e2778f051d" style="color: #00AA00;" class="username-coloured">Yudan Taiteki</a></strong> &raquo; Mon 11.15.2010 9:11 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Of course, don't forget that 发 is also the simplified form of 髪 -- some of the simplifications have resulted in dissimilar characters combing into one.</div>

